# Cloudflare Pages routing rules
#
# Default Cloudflare Pages behavior auto-redirects /foo.html -> /foo with a
# 308 response. That breaks shared "/dlt.html" links when the client has
# transient connectivity issues (the redirect target may resolve to an
# error before the redirected fetch completes).
#
# Force /dlt.html to serve the file directly with 200.
# Syntax: <source> <destination> <status>  (status 200 = rewrite, no redirect)

/dlt.html  /dlt.html  200
/dlt       /dlt.html  200
